betterquesting:10.desc:8: Punch tree, get wood. You know the drill.
You'll need some flint to begin mining stone.
For your first tools, you'll need some TiC stuff.
You can't mine stone with a wooden pickaxe! You'll need a flint one.
Whether it's used to build your first house, or to craft that much less important furnace, you'll need some cobble. Grab a stack.

Welcome to the Kharax Community Pack!

§1(Insert some form of "mission statement" here)

§fHere is some food and armour to get you started!§f
Surprise! Yes, this is a §dBotania §0§7§fbased early game!
No, I'm §4not§f going to say it. Pick up some grout for your smeltery.
Obviously you'll need a furnace, but a house is still important >:(
Time to sear some bricks.
Now you can make some better tools! Craft whatever head you need, it'll complete all the same.
§3§fFor the next "age" and to get metal tools, you'll need §ealuminium brass§r, §rmade from alloying §baluminium §fand §e§4§3§2copper§f.
Remember that aluminium brass? You should, as you probably made it less than a minute ago. You'll need it to properly begin Botania by crafting the petal apothecary.

Now that you can easily make seared bricks, now would be the time to make a seared furnace!

A seared furnace is like a regular furance, but runs on lava, and can smelt many items at once!
Pure Daisies are used to transform various blocks into other blocks, which are then used in crafting recipes.

Wooden Hoppers are a cheaper version of the standard hopper, at the cost of moving items somewhat slower. The recipe is unchanged to encourge earlygame usage.

They are good for earlygame item movement, especially when combined with conveyor belts.

Mana Spreaders are used to move mana, which is created by Mana producing flowers

Refer to the Lexica Botania for greater detail.

The §mStarfur§my§r Starcaller's recipe has been made easier, to encourge earlygame usage, like it's terraria counterpart.

Crafting this item will also net you a mana tablet, to allow you to summon stars with this sword, and autorepair it.

Your first mutliblock machine!

The metal press can be used to create a varity of items, such as plates and wires faster.

It can also be used to create gears.
This forge hammer will allow you to press certain items into other items, such as...
(Or iron + other stuff, anyway). This is the main metal you'll need to get you started in Tech Reborn and NuclearCraft.

EFLNs are a extremely underrated part of Tinker's construct. They are balls that when thrown, will create an explosion on impact. All blocks that are affected by the explosion will drop as items, making them great for mining.

Finally, an upgrade from Casting Channels!

Fluid pipes are crafted in a carpenter, along with some (insert fluid name).

Fluid pumps are useful when pumping in and out of tanks without defined input/output sides, as well as sucking up fluids from the world.

The fluid router will be good to use, as using a liquid container (like a Bucket) in it's GUI will not put the fluid into the slot, but it will configure the Fluid Router to output that fluid through that specific side into a tank when it enters the Fluid Router. You can easily combine and divert fluids with this.

Conveyor Belts are useful for moving items around.

Shift right-clicking will make the Conveyor Belt run up instead of horizontal.

Extracting conveyor belts allow you to pull from inventories without the need of hoppers.
Make wires by cutting some plates with wire cutters or shears.
Used in the creation of mana pools, as well as other items.

Created by dropping certain items (refer to the Lexica Botania) into a pool of mana. 

Used in crafting recipes.

Arcane Archives is a storage mod with a focus on magic, built for the early to midgame.

Even if you are not interested in remote item accessing and storage, there are some items that are worth checking out, such as the Radiant Chest, which a 54 slot chest with a 256 stack size, and the Radiant Trove, which can hold up to 1024 stacks of a single item.
Forestry is good and all, but what about the other (non-Botania) tech mods? To get started on those, you'll need terrasteel.

Pulse mana spreader will only fire when they recive a redstone pulse.

This might be useful in the future...

... Plates! 

Plates will be used to craft a large varity of items, such as machine hulls.

With you new plates, and other resources, you can now craft a mana fluxfield!

Mana fluxfields allow you to turn Botania mana into redstone flux, allowing you to start crafting (and using) some machines!

Don't worry however, Botania isnt going to become irrelevant just because machines are now in play.

1:10.description:8: Will announce your feat to the server
1:10.command:8:
#Script Comment
say Running reward script...
say @s has made their first fluxfield!

betterquesting:10.desc:8:
By combining iron and heat in a high oven, along with 3 other ingredients, you can create steel!


(Check JEI to see what works best for you)
To transfer that RF you're generating, you're going to need some IE wires and connectors. Storing this power, however, is not for a fair while.
For many early game recipes, especially to get further with Botania, the carpenter is needed.
To get started with Forestry, you'll need some sturdy casings. I'm sure you can figure out how to get the bronze.
Now that you have the carpenter, you can craft some other Forestry machines.

betterquesting:10.name:8: Are You Getting Sappy With Me?
betterquesting:10.desc:8:
Mana Sap is an important fluid for much of Botania.

You can also use mana diamonds/pearls to get even better yields.
Yes, back to Botania. While the other Botania staple items are relatively easy to make, for manasteel, an extra step is needed.
Runes are important components for a lot of mid-game Botania stuff. For more information, consult the Lexica Botania.

Well, sort of. The first thing you'll need is an IE Coke Oven. 

Make your brick blocks in the carpenter, along with some mana sap.

(The mana sap is for reinforcement)
To craft your Immersive Engineering electrical machines, you'll need to a new fluid. Right now, the only way to get this is from squeezing creosote.

By using some manastring and a carpenter, you can craft the various forestry backpacks!

What makes these backpacks special is that items will automagicly (get it?) enter said backpack once picked up.

There are various backpacks, and different items are assigned to different backpacks (ores go in the mining backpack, etc).

Backpacks can also be upgraded to hold 45 stacks.

Make yourself a mining backpack, and I will give you another one for your troubles.

With your much stronger metal press, you can now make plates and wires out some more metals, which can be in turn used to create some more powerful wires!



Try not to get zapped.
Used to transform some blocks into dusts.

With a alloy kiln, you can now start to make some more alloys, by combining dusts!

Tough alloy is a big one.
You will need a blueprint, and a engineer's workstation to make molds.

Gears will be needed for making various machines in the future. Place a gear mold on your metal presser and give it some iron to make some plates.

You can automate this process of importing and exporting item easily with conveyor belts.
With your MV wire and current infrastructure, it's time to do more with IE.
Sap will be used for getting rubber for TR cables. Grab a bunch with a treetap.
That steel-making process you have right now is getting a little old... Go ahead and make yourself an IE blast furnace.
The behaviour of the preheaters have been buffed dramatically, making the blast furnace much faster.

Biodiesel is an excellent power source added by IE. This questline will guide you through the process of making it.
Squeeze seeds, get oil.
NEI will tell you what the best items are for you to ferment to get this.

For now, the only way to get rubber is to smelt it. There are better ways to get it later on, however.

Wooden Hoppers are a cheaper version of the standard hopper, at the cost of moving items somewhat slower. The recipe is unchanged to encourge earlygame usage.

They are good for earlygame item movement, especially when combined with conveyor belts.

The copper cables here can be made in the IE press multi, yielding one per ingot. Later on, you can up this rate however.

For now, you can craft these manually, but you'll probably want to make them differently later on...

Drying racks are useful to transforming various items into others.

In this pack, monster jerky can be dried into leather, allowing you to convert rotten flesh into leather early on.

Early on, you are going to be decently limited in your methods of item transportation. However, casting channels can be used to transfer fluids. This can be used for both general fluid transporation, but you can also route one faucet to many seared tables/basins at once.

You will need a large amount of aluminum brass for botantia, so this might be worth considering.
